description: Dataset capturing NSI LOAD LEVEL metrics values and related metadata for 5G core network
author: Ariadni Fyrogeni, University of Patras

metrics.name: s5c Rx Sessions requested to be created
metrics.description: Indicates the average and variance number of PDU session established at the S-NSSAI and the optionally associated network slice instance.

metrics.name: UE Count
metrics.description: Indicates the average and variance number of UE registered at the S-NSSAI and the optionally associated network slice instance.

metrics.name: CPU Percentage
metrics.description: Average usage of virtual CPU.

metrics.name: Memory Usage
metrics.description: Average usage of memory, in MiB.

metrics.name: Number of Exceed Load Level Threshold
metrics.description: Indicates the number of times the resource usage threshold of the network slice instance is reached or exceeded if a threshold value is provided by the consumer.

metrics.name: Exceed Load Level Threshold Indicator
metrics.description: Indicates whether the Load Level Threshold is met or exceeded by the statistics value.

metrics.name: Resource Usage Threshold Cross Time Period
metrics.description: Each element indicates the time elapsed between times each threshold is met or exceeded or crossed. The start time and end time are the exact time stamps of the resource usage threshold is reached or exceeded.
